  "literature_convergence": "PREDICTION: IncF/IncQ/IncN plasmid replicons are MOBILE (conjugative), so AMR<->plasmid co-occurrence should GENERALIZE across held-out clades MORE than the chromosomal-PAI virulence axis did \u2014 mobile elements transfer horizontally between lineages, chromosomal islands do not. A clade-surviving AUC here is the horizontal-co-transfer signal; a collapse would mean the replicon is clade-fixed (vertically inherited on a stable backbone, e.g. the ST131 IncFII resistance plasmid).",
